               <p>RICHARD UNITE. I am a <rs id="t18241202-92-viclabel499" type="occupation">bridle bit maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-92-victim591 t18241202-92-viclabel499"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18241202-92-crimeloc500">Lisle-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-92-crimeloc500" type="placeName" value="Lisle-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-92-crimeloc500" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-92-off497 t18241202-92-crimeloc500"></join>. The prisoner came into my service in March last. Some bridle bits were produced to me by the pawnbrokers. I knew them to be mine - one of my workmen had given me some duplicates, which were found in my shop, which led me to the pawnbrokers.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-92-person592">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HARYETT
